page.title: 06Birds,Agnes,Scilly
page.content: Nesting on Gugh there are Gulls,Terns, Kittiwakes and Oyster Catchers.The Gulls nest on the grass and on the rocks.Sometimes when the sea is rough the nests on the rocks get washed away and then the poor parents have to start again.The Kittiwakes nest on ledges under the cliff and lay 2 eggs before the chicks have to hatch.The Terns and Oyster catchers nest out in the open ,beside rocks where their chicks can hide when they are born.Many rare birds are seen on Agnes ,blown off course during migration in Spring and Autumn.The names of some birds are Bee Eaters , Barn Owls,Oriole and Roller.
